r own transport method (fixer grid). Fixers make decent tanks if necessary and the high end grid armor is pretty damn sweet.<br>
<br>
At level 80 I was able to solo a level 124 mob. Very good offensively and no other class in the game can match a fixer for making cash unless you count very high level tradeskills like nanoprogramming.<br>
<br>
If you do make a fixer go with the SMG/Burst only weapons. Anything else is a waste of time. These would include the low level fixer staple - Mausser Particle Streamer (MPS). <br>
<br>
Assuming you are starting on Rubi-Ka 1 as Omni I could log in  help ya a bit perhaps. I think Ovarrd may be playing a little there also when SWG is a bear to log into.. <br>
<br>
The Enforcer is nice for melee. They do a LOT of damage. <br>
<br>
Martial Artist WAS a great class for damage also - though I hear they nerfed the crit damage and now they are ok.<br>
<br>
Agents are perhaps the hardest class to play since they can become almost any class like a disguise. Which is to say they can actually use other classes skills as well. Interesting class though I never got into it.<br>
<br>
Adventurers - just from listening to other people I could say they appear gimped though I don't know why people say that.<br>
<br>
As you start move your AGG slider to full AGGressive. This will ensure your shooting and casting times are as quick as possible. <p>===================<BR>
Brin - Midgardian Norse Skald<BR>
Ciaran - Always a Dragon Knight <BR><BR>

