any class can solo in AO, and leveling for any class isn't hard. you can get 1-10 levels a day depending if you're grouped and for how long. most missions, you get equipment that you won't even be able to use til later levels, so you never really have to worry about equipment.<br>
the game is set up so that you don't have to worry about grinding, getting loot, or porting around. it's all about fun, and they did one hell of a job.<br>
I'd suggest soldier or agent for most fun to play. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub96.ezboard.com/bdragonknightsdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=waasak>Waasak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Officer</span><br>  Posts: 179<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(12/19/02 7:23:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub96.ezboard.com/fdragonknightsdaocfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: doofus</span><hr size=1> I'm still playing usually on my Enforcer Drenf lately he's lvl 50 in QL 77 Recruit-Issue Omni-Pol Elite gear not too shabby, but best thing is it looks damn good.  And really this game is about the looks.<br>
<br>
Agents are a lot of fun to play from what I understand but don't get all caught up trying to sneak through missions.  Get a run buff from a fixer and blitz it.  Even the agents think sneaking through a mission is a waste.<br>
<br>
So far I have played my MA to 78 an Enforcer to 50 and a Doc to 16 and they all definitely have their upsides and downsides.  MA's are pretty awesome at soloing but I didn't do my IP alottments right and I am hating life at this level with no Yalm it's near impossible to get to some of the mission locations solo without it.  MA's are still good against the mobs in game, but they totally suck for PvP.  I was easily soling missions 15 QL's above my MA up until recently.  They did a change to how melee initatives are calculated so that kind of hosed up dual weilding weapons.  Mobs are parrying a ton right now so MA's using claws really got hit hard because your attack rating suffers when using a claw as an MA.  So in order to do good damage again I had to drop the claw and in turn that has slowed down the rate I do criticals, which in turn has slowed down the total damage output.  All that just so I could hit mobs consistantly again.<br>
<br>
We are on the Atlantean server formerly known as Rubi-Ka 1 and we play on the Omni side.<br>
<br>
I have heard Agents were a ton of fun to play so good luck with that, just about any profession is a lot of fun, except pet classes.  Pet pathing is the number 1 fix list issue for Funcom at the moment and that's a good thing that they are listening to the pet owners finally. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub96.ezboard.com/bdragonknightsdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ci>Ci</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>[GM]</span><br>  Posts: 845<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(12/19/02 8:45:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub96.ezboard.com/fdragonknightsdaocfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.dragonknights.org/ciaaran_head.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Strayfe wears underoos..</span><hr size=1> Only strayfe would want to sneak through a mission and waste valuable money making time when you can blitz it as mach-4 and get it done in 30-60 seconds. As a level 80 fixer who has access to the &quot;fixer grid&quot; (need to complete a fun quest) and the proud owner of a Yalmaha (a flying car that gives you complete 3D movement control - VERY cool and expensive) I can get almost anywhere in the world in less than 3 minutes.<br>
